00:23:45,291 --> 00:23:47,460
We were in elementary school together.

265
00:23:47,631 --> 00:23:49,318
I'm Shoya Ishida.

266
00:24:00,598 --> 00:24:02,027
Where are you going?

267
00:24:02,087 --> 00:24:02,726
Wait!

268
00:24:08,237 --> 00:24:09,417
Please, come back.

269
00:24:13,226 --> 00:24:14,352
Where did she go?

270
00:24:15,126 --> 00:24:15,775
Hey!

271
00:24:20,221 --> 00:24:21,015
H... Hey.

272
00:24:25,314 --> 00:24:27,439
So I...

273
00:24:31,560 --> 00:24:32,836
I came here to give you this.

274
00:24:33,009 --> 00:24:34,504
I....

275
00:24:35,866 --> 00:24:37,446
You left this behind.

276
00:24:42,700 --> 00:24:45,503
Oh, what's that? How do I know sign language?

277
00:24:45,708 --> 00:24:46,932
From a class.

278
00:24:47,300 --> 00:24:49,400
Here you go. It's yours.

279
00:24:53,716 --> 00:24:56,436
I don't even know if you ever wanted to see this again.

280
00:25:01,382 --> 00:25:03,006
I was wondering...

281
00:25:03,840 --> 00:25:06,350
...can me and you...

282
00:25:06,350 --> 00:25:07,203
Shoko,

283
00:25:08,350 --> 00:25:09,860
can we be friends?

284
00:25:10,806 --> 00:25:12,076
Is that an option...

285
00:25:13,290 --> 00:25:15,550
Oh, what did I just say...

286
00:25:17,097 --> 00:25:19,697
That's what you were trying to ask me back in school.

287
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:21,706
I finally understand you.

288
00:25:22,486 --> 00:25:22,861
Oh...

289
00:25:25,991 --> 00:25:27,361
Don't cry.

290
00:25:28,532 --> 00:25:30,176
Please don't cry, Shoko.

291
00:25:37,450 --> 00:25:42,324
I wanted to ask if we could
be friends. Would that be okay?

292
00:25:43,440 --> 00:25:46,500
Sho-Sho,

293
00:25:47,736 --> 00:25:53,072
Sho-Sho, wake up!

294
00:25:53,732 --> 00:25:55,682
Time for breakfast!

295
00:26:00,479 --> 00:26:02,793
Okay Sho, up and at'em!

296
00:26:05,466 --> 00:26:06,856
Good morning, Maria.

297
00:26:08,376 --> 00:26:09,556
Sho-Sho is wake!

298
00:26:27,673 --> 00:26:28,785
I'm heading out.

299
00:26:29,539 --> 00:26:30,839
Bye bye, Mom!

300
00:26:30,864 --> 00:26:32,031
Have a good day dear.

301
00:26:32,960 --> 00:26:35,064
Here, Sbreakfast is served.

302
00:26:36,090 --> 00:26:37,643
Thank you for this meal.

303
00:26:38,329 --> 00:26:39,747
Dig in big guy!

304
00:26:46,056 --> 00:26:48,558
What's got you so bright and cheery this morning?

305
00:26:49,784 --> 00:26:51,260
Because...

306
00:26:52,460 --> 00:26:53,630
I found this!

307
00:26:53,630 --> 00:26:54,490
Oh.

308
00:26:54,860 --> 00:26:57,000
You've been working so hard at your job,

309
00:26:57,000 --> 00:27:00,441
and you even sold your comics, colthes and futon.

310
00:27:01,796 --> 00:27:04,958
I am so lucky to have such a thoughtful son...

311
00:27:07,820 --> 00:27:09,807
But tell me Shoya...

312
00:27:11,266 --> 00:27:13,360
Why would you want to kill yourself?

313
00:27:16,250 --> 00:27:17,740
I just...

314
00:27:17,740 --> 00:27:19,973
don't do a lot of crazy stuff lately.

315
00:27:20,516 --> 00:27:22,506
What can I say... I just...

316
00:27:22,560 --> 00:27:23,850
I knew it...

317
00:27:25,682 --> 00:27:27,782
I knew something was going on with you.

318
00:27:27,807 --> 00:27:29,990
Do not even try to deny it.

319
00:27:30,030 --> 00:27:33,310
Your room is clean for a change.
You cancelled your phone service.

320
00:27:33,310 --> 00:27:36,693
And everything after April's
been torn up from your calendar.

321
00:27:37,390 --> 00:27:40,485
I can't believe it. It's so morbid.

322
00:27:41,130 --> 00:27:44,072
Promise me you won't go through
with it or I'm torching this.

323
00:27:44,401 --> 00:27:48,183
The 1.7 million yen you earned will go to waste.

324
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:52,639
Are you listening to a word I'm saying?

325
00:27:53,213 --> 00:27:53,859
Huh!?

326
00:27:53,986 --> 00:27:56,306
Yeah, don't do anything crazy, mom...

327
00:27:56,345 --> 00:27:58,680
Crazy? You were gonna over yourself.

328
00:27:58,680 --> 00:27:59,819
No! Wait!

329
00:28:00,093 --> 00:28:01,080
I'am sorry mom.

330
00:28:01,080 --> 00:28:03,120
I'm really sorry. I won't do it again

331
00:28:03,120 --> 00:28:05,120
I swear I won't. Please don't burn it.

332
00:28:05,120 --> 00:28:07,331
What are you not gonna do. Please specific.

333
00:28:07,610 --> 00:28:09,539
I promise I'm not going to kill myself.

334
00:28:09,630 --> 00:28:12,040
I swear I won't do it, please believe me.

335
00:28:12,547 --> 00:28:13,920
Do you mean it?

336
00:28:14,197 --> 00:28:15,437
I swear to you!

337
00:28:16,283 --> 00:28:19,692
OK, then I won't burn this...

338
00:28:19,989 --> 00:28:21,058
Mom! Watch out!

339
00:28:22,160 --> 00:28:23,060
Fire!

340
00:28:26,460 --> 00:28:27,740
Give me some water.

341
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:34,781
Smoky!

342
00:28:36,510 --> 00:28:40,820
Yesterday I was planning to jump off
a really tall bridge and kill myself.

343
00:28:41,870 --> 00:28:45,539
I only went to see Shoko
Nishimiya to wrap up any loose ends.

344
00:28:47,610 --> 00:28:51,183
It was hands-down the greatest test of courage ever...

345
00:28:51,960 --> 00:28:53,620
I was supposed to be anyway.

346
00:29:07,477 --> 00:29:09,217
Can we be friends?

347
00:29:14,526 --> 00:29:16,136
World's biggest loser!

348
00:29:16,840 --> 00:29:21,141
On the first day of junior high,
Kazuki makes sure everyone knew...

349
00:29:21,320 --> 00:29:23,627
You should probably stay away from Shoya Ishida.

350
00:29:23,770 --> 00:29:26,635
He's a bully. He's so bad.

351
00:29:26,700 --> 00:29:28,728
A girl had to switch schools.

352
00:29:32,890 --> 00:29:36,679
Like they always say, what goes around comes around.

353
00:29:37,870 --> 00:29:39,634
I knew I really screwed up.

354
00:29:40,406 --> 00:29:42,646
And I needed to pay for being a jerk.

355
00:29:43,956 --> 00:29:47,989
And so I pushed everyone away.

356
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,228
All right everyone.

357
00:30:28,350 --> 00:30:31,696
Make sure to have this translated by next week's class.

358
00:30:41,313 --> 00:30:42,500
Hey Shoya.

359
00:30:43,125 --> 00:30:44,415
H-hi.

360
00:30:44,440 --> 00:30:45,290
Miki...

361
00:30:45,290 --> 00:30:48,042
Have you had a chance to hand in your math notebook yet?

362
00:30:48,165 --> 00:30:49,782
Oh sorry, I forgot.

363
00:30:50,019 --> 00:30:51,162
That's okay.

364
00:30:51,365 --> 00:30:53,321
Just try to hand it in soon all right.

365
00:30:53,626 --> 00:30:54,246
Sorry.

366
00:30:54,271 --> 00:30:55,101
No problem.

367
00:30:58,782 --> 00:31:00,637
Wanna go sit in the courtyard?

368
00:31:02,258 --> 00:31:05,838
Shoya never hangs out with anyone, what a loser.

369
00:31:06,440 --> 00:31:07,632
Didn't you hear about him?

370
00:31:07,680 --> 00:31:09,160
Everyone knows...

371
00:31:09,750 --> 00:31:11,140
No way dude!

372
00:31:12,566 --> 00:31:14,993
Hey check it out he's looking at us again.

373
00:31:15,897 --> 00:31:18,750
I wonder if he gets a lonely
being by himself all the time.

374
00:31:19,676 --> 00:31:20,966
What a total freak!

375
00:31:21,666 --> 00:31:23,186
Why does he bother living?

376
00:31:26,830 --> 00:31:27,780
Oh hey!

377
00:31:28,000 --> 00:31:30,624
I got their new album. You want to check it out?

378
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:31,690
Yeah...

379
00:31:31,847 --> 00:31:34,242
Since you like them I don't anymore.

380
00:31:34,309 --> 00:31:35,800
Yeah Me too.

381
00:31:40,840 --> 00:31:42,322
Yeah, all right.

382
00:31:59,499 --> 00:32:00,199
Huh?

383
00:32:02,680 --> 00:32:04,630
I've seen that head before.

384
00:32:05,811 --> 00:32:07,017
Who is he?

385
00:32:17,883 --> 00:32:19,223
It doesn't matter.

386
00:32:20,110 --> 00:32:22,191
Should I go and see Shoko again?

387
00:32:23,280 --> 00:32:25,272
She said she feeds the carp bread.

388
00:32:26,360 --> 00:32:30,473
But I can't just show up there.
Not after everything I've done.

389
00:32:32,149 --> 00:32:34,751
Should I go and apologize for making her cry.

390
00:32:35,573 --> 00:32:38,126
She did say she's there every Tuesday.

391
00:32:38,890 --> 00:32:40,550
Will is it too creepy?

392
00:32:53,070 --> 00:32:54,985
Hey mom, I'm home.

393
00:33:05,472 --> 00:33:06,841
Hi! Sho.

394
00:33:08,553 --> 00:33:10,407
Oh you scared the crap out of me.

395
00:33:10,720 --> 00:33:11,568
What's up?

396
00:33:13,710 --> 00:33:18,826
I... I'm sorry for burning all your hard-earned money.

397
00:33:19,179 --> 00:33:20,572
I didn't mean to.

398
00:33:22,140 --> 00:33:25,991
Then again you only earn that
money so he could kill yourself.

399
00:33:26,329 --> 00:33:27,788
So I don't want it anyway.

400
00:33:29,565 --> 00:33:32,300
Sorry mom. I'll earn it back.

401
00:33:32,417 --> 00:33:33,790
I konw you will.

402
00:33:33,912 --> 00:33:36,187
But I don't want you to worry too much about it.

403
00:33:36,250 --> 00:33:39,610
In the meantime, how about
some dinner. Who's hungry.

404
00:33:39,662 --> 00:33:40,875
I am hungry!

405
00:33:50,615 --> 00:33:51,801
Tuesday.

406
00:33:57,085 --> 00:33:59,370
Hey, let me borrow your bike.

407
00:33:59,958 --> 00:34:00,785
Me?

408
00:34:01,088 --> 00:34:02,795
What do you need my bicycle for?

409
00:34:02,820 --> 00:34:04,120
That kid I saw at lunch.

410
00:34:04,232 --> 00:34:08,200
I forgot something at home.
So I need your bike to get it.

411
00:34:08,200 --> 00:34:09,720
But I don't even know you.

412
00:34:09,720 --> 00:34:11,711
Why can't you just use your own bike.

413
00:34:13,336 --> 00:34:15,816
I'm asking you because I don't have one.

414
00:34:16,617 --> 00:34:18,700
No... please don't.

415
00:34:18,700 --> 00:34:20,040
Give me that.

416
00:34:20,040 --> 00:34:22,885
I have been robbed! Somebody help me!

417
00:34:24,568 --> 00:34:26,750
Anybody up there?

418
00:34:26,750 --> 00:34:28,990
Why don't anyone help me?

419
00:34:29,116 --> 00:34:30,216
Shut up!

420
00:34:30,780 --> 00:34:32,280
God you're annoying,

421
00:34:33,740 --> 00:34:36,320
just let go of the dam bike already!

422
00:34:38,030 --> 00:34:40,428
Do you want to borrow mine? It's over there.

423
00:34:40,703 --> 00:34:44,375
Yeah, thanks man. You are godsend.

424
00:34:48,200 --> 00:34:49,568
Of course he stole it...

425
00:34:51,260 --> 00:34:54,902
And today's Tuesday of all days.

426
00:34:55,502 --> 00:34:58,283
So is that a sign that I should just leave her alone?

427
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:01,087
It's not like I can't just walk there,

428
00:35:01,130 --> 00:35:03,627
but it's like I'm being told not to go.

429
00:35:04,879 --> 00:35:06,299
I need a good reason.

430
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:11,888
Something real.

431
00:35:13,960 --> 00:35:16,310
It doesn't look like I'm trying too hard.

432
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:24,071
Half off fluffy new bread.

433
00:35:25,046 --> 00:35:25,831
This is it!

434
00:35:27,457 --> 00:35:29,320
Uh... Is Shoko Nishimiya here?

435
00:35:29,470 --> 00:35:30,600
She's not here.

436
00:35:31,209 --> 00:35:32,680
She's right there.

437
00:35:32,859 --> 00:35:33,968
Not her.

438
00:35:35,116 --> 00:35:38,129
There's nobody here named Shoko.

439
00:35:38,250 --> 00:35:40,097
Who are you anyway.

440
00:35:40,190 --> 00:35:43,112
I mean are you actually a friend of hers?

441
00:35:44,010 --> 00:35:44,954
Thought so.

442
00:35:51,758 --> 00:35:53,430
Nothing to worry about.

443
00:35:54,760 --> 00:35:56,882
There was a rat in the hallway.

444
00:35:57,256 --> 00:35:59,189
A really gross one.

445
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,397
Don't worry. He won't be back.

446
00:36:12,700 --> 00:36:14,343
Can we be friends...

447
00:36:29,690 --> 00:36:30,727
What...?

448
00:36:32,169 --> 00:36:33,959
Oh, found him! Hey! You!

449
00:36:34,032 --> 00:36:35,579
Hey! You!

450
00:36:35,679 --> 00:36:37,938
Over here! Look! Check it out!

451
00:36:37,963 --> 00:36:40,860
I found your bike! This is yous, isn't it?

452
00:36:42,566 --> 00:36:44,523
What a perfect timing!

453
00:36:44,972 --> 00:36:47,312
It's a good thing you had your address on it.

454
00:36:48,540 --> 00:36:51,521
That's great! But where did you find it?

455
00:36:51,661 --> 00:36:54,016
That jerk dumped it in a rice field.

456
00:36:54,192 --> 00:36:56,386
May it took me forever to find it.

457
00:36:56,737 --> 00:37:00,017
Thank goodness I did and I found you too.

458
00:37:06,956 --> 00:37:08,464
Is something wrong?

459
00:37:08,891 --> 00:37:09,498
What?

460
00:37:09,610 --> 00:37:10,593
Nothing...

461
00:37:11,020 --> 00:37:13,414
Tell me. What's your name anyway?

462
00:37:13,555 --> 00:37:19,341
But...? We don't already know?
Tomohiro Nagatsuka. I sit behind you.

463
00:37:20,460 --> 00:37:21,980
Right I knew that.

464
00:37:22,635 --> 00:37:25,235
It's really good bread and do
you want to split it with me?

465
00:37:25,506 --> 00:37:26,319
Shoya!

466
00:37:27,880 --> 00:37:29,025
Hey there! Shoya.

467
00:37:30,475 --> 00:37:31,442
Good morning!

468
00:37:31,702 --> 00:37:33,562
Ah... morning.

469
00:37:36,418 --> 00:37:37,604
Hey, Shoya.

470
00:37:38,060 --> 00:37:40,346
Do you want to hang out with me after school today?

471
00:37:40,546 --> 00:37:42,226
I mean... since we are friends now.

472
00:37:43,422 --> 00:37:46,055
Shoya over here! I saved you a seat.

473
00:38:08,860 --> 00:38:10,724
What's troubling you, Ya-sho?

474
00:38:12,495 --> 00:38:13,488
It's nothing.

475
00:38:13,800 --> 00:38:14,676
Who's "Ya-sho"?

476
00:38:14,780 --> 00:38:16,798
It's your nickname, shows that we're close.

477
00:38:16,823 --> 00:38:17,881
Oh cool!

478
00:38:20,033 --> 00:38:22,402
Well, so tell me what's troubling you?

479
00:38:22,510 --> 00:38:25,737
You know you can tell me anything.
That's what best friends are for.

480
00:38:30,002 --> 00:38:32,259
Hey, do you mind if I ask you something?

481
00:38:32,947 --> 00:38:35,377
What does it mean to become someone's friend?

482
00:38:36,090 --> 00:38:39,940
Like it. Is there some sort of
friendship process you go through,

483
00:38:40,383 --> 00:38:43,037
or like do you need any specific qualifications?

484
00:38:44,382 --> 00:38:45,932
Hey, Ya-sho.

485
00:38:49,793 --> 00:38:51,066
Give me your hand, okay?

486
00:38:56,058 --> 00:38:56,865
Hey, hey.

487
00:39:04,330 --> 00:39:08,728
Now you and I is friends.
It could be simple as that. See...

488
00:39:09,035 --> 00:39:12,412
Friendship don't got to do with rules or qualifications.

489
00:39:12,477 --> 00:39:14,227
Because it's about something deeper.

490
00:39:14,590 --> 00:39:17,446
A bond and you just can't break that.

491
00:39:18,560 --> 00:39:19,281
Capeesh?

492
00:39:21,770 --> 00:39:23,379
She is not here.

493
00:39:23,848 --> 00:39:25,053
She is right there.

494
00:39:25,145 --> 00:39:25,885
She is not!

495
00:39:25,931 --> 00:39:28,618
Oh, I see it. I think Maybe...

496
00:39:28,811 --> 00:39:31,104
Shoko's my girlfriend, okay?

497
00:39:33,130 --> 00:39:34,774
Oh... well... that sucks...

498
00:39:35,000 --> 00:39:38,652
Oh... not for me personally
because I brought her all this bread.

499
00:39:39,000 --> 00:39:39,786
But...

500
00:39:40,010 --> 00:39:42,880
I didn't know shoko was into younger guys.

501
00:39:43,095 --> 00:39:46,151
I mean nothing against you I
just I never would have guessed.

502
00:39:46,360 --> 00:39:48,369
Can you at least give her
the bread? It's really good.

503
00:39:48,394 --> 00:39:53,811
Litsen! If you are just here to make
yourself feel better, you might as well leave.

504
00:39:57,576 --> 00:39:59,218
If you'll excuse me...

505
00:39:59,991 --> 00:40:00,800
Goodbye.

506
00:40:02,115 --> 00:40:03,299
Listening boy!

507
00:40:03,423 --> 00:40:07,011
What's your problem? My friend here
just wants to see miss Shoko okay?

508
00:40:07,064 --> 00:40:09,644
So stop being so stubborn. Go get her!

509
00:40:09,757 --> 00:40:11,898
Seriously, what are you even doing here?

510
00:40:13,053 --> 00:40:13,920
I followed you.

511
00:40:14,060 --> 00:40:15,784
Friends have each other's backs.

512
00:40:16,712 --> 00:40:21,078
The shitty stalker has his own shitty
stalker. Makes you two a load of crap.

513
00:40:21,922 --> 00:40:24,452
What? Oh yeah what was that?

514
00:40:25,292 --> 00:40:27,571
What did you say...!

515
00:40:28,037 --> 00:40:29,789
I called you are abull shit...

516
00:40:30,159 --> 00:40:32,585
That doesn't sound good.
What's going on out there?

517
00:40:32,720 --> 00:40:34,583
That's sounds like Yuzuru.

518
00:40:35,580 --> 00:40:37,316
Oh, no. They are fighting.

519
00:40:37,470 --> 00:40:39,115
Would you please clam down.

520
00:40:40,347 --> 00:40:43,880
Seriously man, don't worry about it. Let us get out here.

521
00:40:44,831 --> 00:40:48,319
Oh hello? Aren't you the nice boy from the other day?

522
00:40:48,472 --> 00:40:52,371
It wasn't me. It must been some one else...

523
00:40:52,396 --> 00:40:54,362
Sorry buddy, you are on your own!

524
00:40:58,606 --> 00:40:59,931
Hey! They're gone!

525
00:41:00,439 --> 00:41:03,006
Great he got to see her after all.

526
00:41:06,198 --> 00:41:07,180
What are you doing?

527
00:41:07,180 --> 00:41:09,271
You are spying on Shoko and Ya-sho?

528
00:41:09,580 --> 00:41:11,270
Hand it over! I want to see.

529
00:41:13,980 --> 00:41:16,590
Ya-sho sure does talk with his hands a lot.

530
00:41:16,617 --> 00:41:18,535
It's called sign language, dumbass.

531
00:41:18,560 --> 00:41:20,628
What? Oh wow!

532
00:41:21,049 --> 00:41:23,562
I'm telling you my man's got real skills.

533
00:41:23,929 --> 00:41:25,664
Do you understand sign?

534
00:41:26,030 --> 00:41:27,256
