803
00:59:09,800 --> 00:59:11,980
And how long will you be staying with us.

804
00:59:11,980 --> 00:59:13,640
One hour? I guess.

805
00:59:15,230 --> 00:59:16,540
I have a coupon...

806
00:59:16,540 --> 00:59:18,697
Oh good! Right this way.

807
00:59:19,233 --> 00:59:21,673
Crap! He actually came...

808
00:59:23,040 --> 00:59:25,468
This is not what I imagined.

809
00:59:26,800 --> 00:59:29,307
There cats... what were you expecting?

810
00:59:29,380 --> 00:59:31,735
Well have you ever been to a place like this?

811
00:59:31,770 --> 00:59:34,861
What? No, I never. I came here for you man.

812
00:59:34,886 --> 00:59:36,994
I wanted to help you reunite with your friend...

813
00:59:37,320 --> 00:59:39,475
and speaking of old friends.

814
00:59:39,573 --> 00:59:40,852
Where is she, anyway?

815
00:59:41,432 --> 00:59:44,047
I wouldn't exactly call this girl a friend.

816
00:59:44,140 --> 00:59:45,085
You wouldn't?

817
00:59:45,458 --> 00:59:48,857
A lot of stuff happened when we were in sixth grade.

818
00:59:48,973 --> 00:59:51,457
To be honesty this whole thing's kind of awkward.

819
00:59:53,207 --> 00:59:54,607
She isn't here.

820
00:59:58,814 --> 01:00:00,427
Wanna take off then?

821
01:00:15,680 --> 01:00:17,053
A bug!

822
01:00:17,360 --> 01:00:18,986
Oh what are you doing here huh?

823
01:00:19,420 --> 01:00:21,261
I came over to play with Maria.

824
01:00:22,040 --> 01:00:25,024
Hey uh, do you think shoka would like this?

825
01:00:27,370 --> 01:00:28,284
Kitty!

826
01:00:30,349 --> 01:00:32,349
I brought you a present, Shoko!

827
01:00:47,363 --> 01:00:48,736
What happened...

828
01:00:52,566 --> 01:00:54,294
I'm just gonna leave this here.

829
01:01:02,810 --> 01:01:03,531
What?

830
01:01:03,813 --> 01:01:05,993
N--Naoka...

831
01:01:06,520 --> 01:01:06,860
What...

832
01:01:06,989 --> 01:01:08,274
Go, go!

833
01:01:09,207 --> 01:01:10,847
Hey what are you doing!?

834
01:01:10,880 --> 01:01:12,497
Long time no see!

835
01:01:12,659 --> 01:01:14,430
Yeah. Long time no see.

836
01:01:17,486 --> 01:01:18,456
Huh?

837
01:01:20,069 --> 01:01:22,488
Wait a minute. Isn't the deaf girl?

838
01:01:23,386 --> 01:01:24,960
Still alone.

839
01:01:25,960 --> 01:01:27,130
Poor thing!

840
01:01:28,686 --> 01:01:31,906
Seriously Shoya. It really has been way too long.

841
01:01:32,000 --> 01:01:33,220
Let's hang out soon.

842
01:01:33,373 --> 01:01:35,404
No I don't think so.

843
01:01:35,580 --> 01:01:37,340
Well, you really hate me, don't you?

844
01:01:37,340 --> 01:01:37,939
What?

845
01:01:38,690 --> 01:01:40,762
No I never said that.

846
01:01:41,937 --> 01:01:43,229
You konw what Shoya,

847
01:01:43,450 --> 01:01:46,410
I always thought I should have
made more of an effort to talk to you.

848
01:01:46,410 --> 01:01:49,171
I'm sorry about everything
that happened when we were kids.

849
01:01:49,310 --> 01:01:51,651
It's not that big of a deal.

850
01:01:53,690 --> 01:01:54,584
Hey Naoka,

851
01:01:55,343 --> 01:01:56,119
get off.

852
01:02:02,910 --> 01:02:04,732
That's purse from our cafe.

853
01:02:05,080 --> 01:02:07,360
Where did that deaf freak get it from.

854
01:02:07,840 --> 01:02:09,207
I gave it to her.

855
01:02:09,586 --> 01:02:11,922
Oh... I see.

856
01:02:16,419 --> 01:02:17,197
Later.

857
01:02:17,966 --> 01:02:18,739
Yeah.

858
01:02:24,077 --> 01:02:24,837
Naoka?

859
01:02:25,210 --> 01:02:29,040
Hey there Shoko long time no see!
Someone was likely tracking you.

860
01:02:29,040 --> 01:02:29,640
Stop!!

861
01:02:29,710 --> 01:02:31,880
That's weird. There's only one of them.

862
01:02:32,064 --> 01:02:34,070
Naoka! What do you think you're doing.

863
01:02:36,200 --> 01:02:38,936
Thought we'd have a game a
catch, just like when we were kids.

864
01:02:45,424 --> 01:02:47,364
I'm so sorry Shoko.

865
01:02:49,061 --> 01:02:52,830
No freakin way, you gotta be kidding me.

866
01:02:52,830 --> 01:02:54,176
Hold on, wait a minute.

867
01:02:54,300 --> 01:02:56,582
Don't tell me you guys are actually going out?

868
01:02:56,702 --> 01:02:59,148
What!? what are you talking about?

869
01:02:59,381 --> 01:03:00,595
We're just friends.

870
01:03:00,840 --> 01:03:01,945
Just friends?

871
01:03:02,220 --> 01:03:04,044
That's hilarious.

872
01:03:04,069 --> 01:03:11,375
Are you telling me you are now besties with the
girl used to bully? I can't believe it. That's crazy.

873
01:03:12,490 --> 01:03:15,431
Let me guess, are you trying to make amends?

874
01:03:15,470 --> 01:03:16,611
Not really.

875
01:03:16,700 --> 01:03:18,172
Ha ha.

876
01:03:18,199 --> 01:03:20,974
Too funny, what's gotten into you?

877
01:03:23,880 --> 01:03:27,056
Well, I'll leave you to your fake friendship thing.

878
01:03:27,142 --> 01:03:29,850
Ha ha ha.

879
01:03:35,007 --> 01:03:37,093
You want to know what we were talking about?

880
01:03:37,966 --> 01:03:40,146
Nothing, don't worry about it.

881
01:03:41,130 --> 01:03:42,709
Look I gotta take off.

882
01:03:43,470 --> 01:03:44,541
See you.

883
01:04:06,090 --> 01:04:07,580
Yuzuru,

884
01:04:09,420 --> 01:04:10,557
time to get up.

885
01:04:10,780 --> 01:04:13,518
I'm up, you startled me awake.

886
01:04:13,610 --> 01:04:15,084
Get off bed, breakfast...

887
01:04:15,109 --> 01:04:16,777
Wait! Before you go...

888
01:04:17,126 --> 01:04:18,240
What's up?

889
01:04:20,651 --> 01:04:24,475
Your hair today it's in a ponytail.

890
01:04:24,587 --> 01:04:25,530
Are you...?

891
01:04:27,880 --> 01:04:29,413
What a weird face!

892
01:04:33,780 --> 01:04:35,716
Shoya will love the new dew.

893
01:04:37,120 --> 01:04:39,183
<i>"So much carp. Shortage ofbread
and feeding manpower.You MUST come."</i>

894
01:04:47,941 --> 01:04:48,634
Huh?

895
01:04:50,940 --> 01:04:52,186
Oh, Shoko.

896
01:04:52,840 --> 01:04:54,441
She's wearing a ponytail.

897
01:05:10,000 --> 01:05:11,515
Where are you going, Shoya?

898
01:05:12,120 --> 01:05:14,245
What was that? Where am I going?

899
01:05:15,500 --> 01:05:16,946
To the bakery.

900
01:05:17,540 --> 01:05:20,818
Yuzuru asked me to get some bread to feed the carp.

901
01:05:20,940 --> 01:05:24,795
But you already have some bread. I bet
she only wants more so she can eat it.

902
01:05:24,848 --> 01:05:27,160
You don't have to buy her anymore. I
can't believe she made you do that for her!

903
01:05:27,160 --> 01:05:28,286
Wait. Just...

904
01:05:28,520 --> 01:05:29,546
Can you sign it?

905
01:05:31,330 --> 01:05:34,222
Is my voice weird?

906
01:05:34,293 --> 01:05:35,029
Yes.

907
01:05:37,672 --> 01:05:39,469
Oh, I'me sorry. I didn't...

908
01:05:40,480 --> 01:05:43,487
Your voice sounds totally okay.

909
01:05:44,660 --> 01:05:47,080
I'm gonna get some bread.

910
01:05:48,446 --> 01:05:49,632
Be right back.

911
01:05:54,337 --> 01:05:55,137
Huh?

912
01:05:56,126 --> 01:05:57,303
What are you doing？

913
01:06:06,020 --> 01:06:07,427
Present for me?

914
01:06:07,713 --> 01:06:08,733
Wow, thanks.

915
01:06:09,093 --> 01:06:09,855
Can I open it?

916
01:06:12,227 --> 01:06:13,350
Like right now?

917
01:06:16,100 --> 01:06:17,464
What are these things?

918
01:06:21,726 --> 01:06:23,250
Thank you so much.

919
01:06:29,980 --> 01:06:30,617
What's that?

920
01:06:30,642 --> 01:06:32,070
Something about these?

921
01:06:34,480 --> 01:06:35,658
I... ige... moo...

922
01:06:42,031 --> 01:06:42,778
Huh?...

923
01:06:46,640 --> 01:06:48,998
I love you!

924
01:06:57,920 --> 01:06:58,789
The moon?

925
01:07:02,320 --> 01:07:04,190
It is pretty, isn't it?

926
01:07:09,812 --> 01:07:10,805
Where are you going?

927
01:07:14,860 --> 01:07:18,040
<i>"How about we go out and see a movie now?"</i>

928
01:07:19,891 --> 01:07:21,417
Can I ask you something?

929
01:07:21,800 --> 01:07:23,517
Do you think they look like the moon?

930
01:07:24,563 --> 01:07:27,012
Let's see... well they don't look like the moon.

931
01:07:27,620 --> 01:07:28,505
Hummm.

932
01:07:29,100 --> 01:07:30,247
Candy!

933
01:07:30,360 --> 01:07:32,084
I'm pretty sure these things aren't candy.

934
01:07:32,666 --> 01:07:34,463
Shoko gave these to me as a present.

935
01:07:34,867 --> 01:07:36,425
I have no idea what they are.

936
01:07:38,639 --> 01:07:39,568
Huh?

937
01:07:41,220 --> 01:07:42,230
Oh...

938
01:07:43,473 --> 01:07:45,293
Are you okay? What happened?

939
01:07:47,940 --> 01:07:49,360
<i>"I said I like you to Ishida-kun"</i>

940
01:07:49,480 --> 01:07:51,160
Ah! You what...!

941
01:07:53,880 --> 01:07:55,130
<i>"But he couldn't understand what I said."</i>

942
01:07:55,345 --> 01:07:56,367
Huh...

943
01:08:04,007 --> 01:08:05,947
Wow, check out your hair. It's different.

944
01:08:05,972 --> 01:08:07,680
What made you decide to change it?

945
01:08:07,680 --> 01:08:11,075
Do you have a hot day? Whatever
it is, you should keep it like this.

946
01:08:11,100 --> 01:08:12,740
Stop it you guys.

947
01:08:12,925 --> 01:08:17,992
You're making me blush. I just didn't
have any time to do it. That's all.

948
01:08:19,120 --> 01:08:20,447
Well. I think it looks good.

949
01:08:20,520 --> 01:08:22,653
Hi, Miki. I've got a question.

950
01:08:22,880 --> 01:08:24,610
Why did you suddenly change your hair?

951
01:08:24,987 --> 01:08:27,372
Hmmm... what do you mean?

952
01:08:27,660 --> 01:08:30,475
It's not like I need any particular reason.

953
01:08:30,829 --> 01:08:33,763
Girls just like to change things up sometimes. You know.

954
01:08:34,739 --> 01:08:35,535
I see.

955
01:08:37,100 --> 01:08:37,938
What is it?

956
01:08:38,860 --> 01:08:43,468
The other days the Toshi told me he thought
you'd be a pretty cool guy to hang out with!

957
01:08:43,960 --> 01:08:44,867
Huh?

958
01:08:52,375 --> 01:08:54,795
Who are you and tell us the nature of your business.

959
01:08:54,820 --> 01:08:56,967
Nice to meet you. Miyoko Sahara.

960
01:08:57,180 --> 01:08:58,807
Hi. Satoshi Mashiba.

961
01:08:58,919 --> 01:09:01,216
Cut it out! Stop doing that over my head.

962
01:09:01,420 --> 01:09:04,020
Miyoko! It feels like it's been a million years!

963
01:09:04,020 --> 01:09:05,821
Hey! If Shoko coming today?

964
01:09:06,080 --> 01:09:07,722
No. She's a stomachache.

965
01:09:07,855 --> 01:09:10,040
Umm... that's weird.

966
01:09:10,140 --> 01:09:11,720
I hope she's not avoiding me.

967
01:09:11,875 --> 01:09:12,630
How come?

968
01:09:12,907 --> 01:09:15,429
She was trying to tell me something the other day.

969
01:09:15,553 --> 01:09:17,989
I just could not understand what she was saying.

970
01:09:18,160 --> 01:09:20,410
What exactly did she say to you?

971
01:09:20,940 --> 01:09:21,652
The moon.

972
01:09:21,880 --> 01:09:22,325
Pff!

973
01:09:22,440 --> 01:09:26,182
It's an easy enough word but her
saying it didn't make any sense.

974
01:09:26,766 --> 01:09:28,637
I bet she was so annoyed.

975
01:09:28,786 --> 01:09:31,646
Well if you really want to know how she feels about you.

976
01:09:31,680 --> 01:09:33,482
Then I suggest you just ask her out.

977
01:09:33,580 --> 01:09:35,870
If she says no, you will have your answer.

978
01:09:35,940 --> 01:09:37,210
I guess that you're right.

979
01:09:41,269 --> 01:09:44,279
<i>"We are planning to go to the amusement
park, I was thinking maybe we can go together?"</i>

980
01:09:59,280 --> 01:10:01,779
Come on! Lets all go on the big one first.

981
01:10:01,880 --> 01:10:03,780
Everyone stick together so we don't get separated man!

982
01:10:03,780 --> 01:10:06,118
Why did she actually act like a chaperone or something.

983
01:10:06,260 --> 01:10:07,032
Who knows?

984
01:10:07,420 --> 01:10:08,300
Shoya.

985
01:10:09,440 --> 01:10:10,920
Who's that? Over there.

986
01:10:10,920 --> 01:10:11,670
Oh!

987
01:10:12,600 --> 01:10:14,814
Why is she acting so chummy with Shoko?

988
01:10:15,040 --> 01:10:17,249
Naoka?... Why she's here?

989
01:10:18,560 --> 01:10:20,520
Is she like a friend or something?

990
01:10:21,194 --> 01:10:21,742
Yeah!

991
01:10:22,145 --> 01:10:23,466
From elementary school.

992
01:10:24,607 --> 01:10:25,254
Hmmmm...

993
01:10:30,340 --> 01:10:32,140
Hey... mind if I sit here?

994
01:10:32,140 --> 01:10:33,850
Not at all. Go right ahead.

995
01:10:36,340 --> 01:10:37,665
I might be scary.

996
01:10:38,180 --> 01:10:40,326
Okay everybody, are you ready?

997
01:10:40,400 --> 01:10:41,800
Yeah!!

998
01:10:41,840 --> 01:10:43,741
Then hold on tight.

999
01:10:45,880 --> 01:10:49,468
Miyoko, so are you like cool with Naoka now?

1000
01:10:49,540 --> 01:10:50,321
Huh?

1001
01:10:50,843 --> 01:10:51,845
Oh, sure!

1002
01:10:51,940 --> 01:10:54,464
We're actually both in the design department at school.

1003
01:10:55,320 --> 01:10:58,703
Now it's got great taste. I've learned a lot from her.

1004
01:11:00,540 --> 01:11:04,945
You know, when we were in elementary
school. I was way to scared to ride this.

1005
01:11:04,980 --> 01:11:06,800
I was such a coward back then.

1006
01:11:08,939 --> 01:11:12,399
But then, one day, I looked at it differently.

1007
01:11:13,170 --> 01:11:17,120
I was going to wait until after the
ride to decide whether it's scary or not.

1008
01:11:20,007 --> 01:11:22,387
Can't help feeling little scary though.

1009
01:11:23,680 --> 01:11:25,035
Here we go!

1010
01:11:45,780 --> 01:11:47,520
Oh... oh no!

1011
01:11:47,986 --> 01:11:50,670
Poor Shoko, your legs are shaking.

1012
01:11:51,529 --> 01:11:53,692
Are you okay?

1013
01:11:54,290 --> 01:11:55,212
Ha ha.

1014
01:11:55,780 --> 01:11:58,745
That's pretty impressive. I didn't know you can sign it!

1015
01:11:58,880 --> 01:12:01,722
You must have worked really hard to learn sign language.

1016
01:12:01,800 --> 01:12:02,675
Huh?

1017
01:12:06,540 --> 01:12:08,940
Hey get your dirty paws off my Ya-sho.

1018
01:12:08,940 --> 01:12:10,280
Who said you could touch it Huh?

1019
01:12:10,280 --> 01:12:11,968
Dude! I was just being friendly.

1020
01:12:13,760 --> 01:12:15,500
Well go be friendly with someone else.

1021
01:12:15,500 --> 01:12:18,040
Nagatsuka you really creak me.

1022
01:12:18,065 --> 01:12:20,729
Ya-sho is my friend I've got my eye on you. You better...

1023
01:12:20,754 --> 01:12:22,862
Hey, is that your real hair?

1024
01:12:23,700 --> 01:12:24,473
No, get off...!

1025
01:12:25,568 --> 01:12:26,614
I'm not joking.

1026
01:12:26,807 --> 01:12:27,667
What's so funny!

1027
01:12:28,080 --> 01:12:29,167
Is this...?

1028
01:12:29,920 --> 01:12:31,860
Faster it Satoshi! They are catching up!

1029
01:12:31,860 --> 01:12:34,540
We can do this, Ya-sho. Come on! Pedal harder!

1030
01:12:34,540 --> 01:12:35,720
What is this...?

1031
01:12:36,760 --> 01:12:37,782
Is it okay...?

1032
01:12:38,533 --> 01:12:40,733
Am I allowed to have this much fun?

1033
01:12:41,767 --> 01:12:44,645
This feels so... familiar.

1034
01:12:46,159 --> 01:12:47,229
Great catch, funny.

1035
01:12:47,263 --> 01:12:50,170
Oh yeah... It almost feels like...

1036
01:12:51,106 --> 01:12:52,465
...like real friends!

1037
01:12:57,881 --> 01:12:58,947
Hey Shoya!

1038
01:13:00,081 --> 01:13:02,655
I'am hungry. I feel like some takoyaki.

1039
01:13:02,779 --> 01:13:03,959
Come with me to get some.

1040
01:13:04,000 --> 01:13:06,254
Ah... I'm not... Hey! Hey! Wait!

1041
01:13:07,820 --> 01:13:10,392
Here you go. One takoyaki.

1042
01:13:10,560 --> 01:13:11,552
Thank you.

1043
01:13:11,680 --> 01:13:12,479
And Naoka!

1044
01:13:13,460 --> 01:13:15,664
You need to learn mind your own business.

1045
01:13:23,431 --> 01:13:26,386
Ka... Kazuki...?

1046
01:13:31,490 --> 01:13:33,177
Shoya where are you going?

1047
01:13:35,880 --> 01:13:37,598
I'll text you later okay?

1048
01:13:38,760 --> 01:13:39,877
Hey wait up!

1049
01:13:41,420 --> 01:13:42,772
Are you mad at me?

1050
01:13:43,140 --> 01:13:44,520
No I'm not.

1051
01:13:45,448 --> 01:13:47,180
I'm fine, yeah.

1052
01:13:47,540 --> 01:13:48,495
I just thought

1053
01:13:48,880 --> 01:13:50,841
maybe you guys could be friends.

1054
01:13:50,940 --> 01:13:52,636
You know, like you used to be.

1055
01:13:53,504 --> 01:13:57,983
I guess I was hoping once you guys actually
saw each other everything would be okay.

1056
01:13:58,110 --> 01:13:59,891
Don't do me any favors, okay?

1057
01:14:01,417 --> 01:14:01,824
Oops.

1058
01:14:03,932 --> 01:14:04,559
Wait...

1059
01:14:05,869 --> 01:14:08,009
I did the exactly same things...

1060
01:14:13,093 --> 01:14:15,364
You and I are more alike than you think you know.

1061
01:14:15,548 --> 01:14:16,795
No. We are not.

1062
01:14:16,960 --> 01:14:18,087
Yes we are.

1063
01:14:18,386 --> 01:14:19,821
We're nothing alike.

1064
01:14:23,720 --> 01:14:24,417
You know,

1065
01:14:24,460 --> 01:14:27,987
If Shoko hadn't shown up, we would
all still be friends and be happy.

1066
01:14:30,239 --> 01:14:31,530
You don't know that.

1067
01:14:31,740 --> 01:14:33,652
Oh, come on. Just admit it.

1068
01:14:33,960 --> 01:14:35,240
If it wasn't for her,

1069
01:14:35,240 --> 01:14:38,036
things wouldn't have gotten
all weird between Miyoko and me.

1070
01:14:38,800 --> 01:14:41,687
And then you wouldn't have stopped
being friends with Kazuki either.

1071
01:14:42,776 --> 01:14:46,082
I just want to go back to the way
things were, before she showed up.

1072
01:14:46,142 --> 01:14:50,761
Kazuki and I... That was
me. I run out on my own.

1073
01:14:51,580 --> 01:14:53,302
Shoya, tell me the truth.

1074
01:14:53,615 --> 01:14:54,630
Do you hate me?

1075
01:14:54,757 --> 01:14:55,657
Probably.

1076
01:14:58,000 --> 01:15:00,504
Fine! Time for a ride on the ferriswheel.

1077
01:15:00,900 --> 01:15:02,837
I'll go see if Shoko wants to come with me.

1078
01:15:03,197 --> 01:15:03,883
Hey!

1079
01:15:04,394 --> 01:15:05,227
Huh?

1080
01:15:05,352 --> 01:15:08,287
Shoko, you've got to come ride the ferriswheel with me.

1081
01:15:08,387 --> 01:15:09,680
Cut it out! Naoka!

1082
01:15:09,866 --> 01:15:12,186
If you guys are going, can you take my camera.

1083
01:15:12,400 --> 01:15:14,612
I want to ride the roller coaster again.

1084
01:15:38,764 --> 01:15:40,403
Oh, hi Yuzuru!

1085
01:15:40,576 --> 01:15:42,943
Come on in. Shoya is upstairs in his room.

1086
01:15:43,896 --> 01:15:44,523
Wow.

1087
01:15:45,039 --> 01:15:47,099
I got top secret video for you.

1088
01:15:48,280 --> 01:15:50,581
A video from the ferriswheel?

1089
01:15:50,633 --> 01:15:51,087
Yeah.

1090
01:15:51,741 --> 01:15:53,120
How would you get it?

1091
01:15:53,240 --> 01:15:54,035
Spying.

1092
01:15:54,088 --> 01:15:54,738
What?

1093
01:15:59,940 --> 01:16:02,060
I want you to listen to me carefully.

1094
01:16:02,460 --> 01:16:04,044
I hate you.

1095
01:16:08,493 --> 01:16:09,957
Put that thing away.

1096
01:16:10,367 --> 01:16:13,363
I'm going to speak slowly so you can understand.

1097
01:16:13,575 --> 01:16:15,678
And I'll listen everything you have to say.

1098
01:16:18,068 --> 01:16:20,523
I'll admit that in elementary school,

1099
01:16:20,583 --> 01:16:23,464
I had no idea what things were like for you.

1100
01:16:23,784 --> 01:16:27,170
It's not like you tried to understand
what I was going through either.

1101
01:16:27,497 --> 01:16:28,694
You know what I mean.

1102
01:16:29,006 --> 01:16:32,066
And instead of getting a clue like a normal person,

1103
01:16:32,095 --> 01:16:35,334
You just kept giving me that stupid notebook of yours.

1104
01:16:35,416 --> 01:16:37,329
You're always being so weird.

1105
01:16:37,442 --> 01:16:39,820
And you would apologize all the time for everything.

1106
01:16:40,380 --> 01:16:42,037
So I tried a different approach.

1107
01:16:42,120 --> 01:16:43,840
I ignored you and blew you off.

1108
01:16:44,063 --> 01:16:47,155
That was my way of telling you that
I didn't want to hang out with you.

1109
01:16:47,420 --> 01:16:48,195
But nope,

1110
01:16:48,340 --> 01:16:52,333
you just kept coming around with
your stupid book and your stupid signs

1111
01:16:52,358 --> 01:16:56,447
you're so clueless then you had
to go run crying to the grown-ups.

1112
01:16:56,794 --> 01:17:02,428
You got Shoya it in trouble and that's how he
ended up losing every single one of his friends.

1113
01:17:02,460 --> 01:17:06,825
You pretty much ruined everything
for everyone, you get that right.

1114
01:17:08,513 --> 01:17:09,770
I... I'm sorry...

1115
01:17:09,952 --> 01:17:14,171
God you still don't get it I'm not
looking for nother apology from you.

1116
01:17:14,737 --> 01:17:16,584
We were both going through a lot,

1117
01:17:16,766 --> 01:17:19,730
and I don't think either of us
could have done anything differently.

1118
01:17:20,446 --> 01:17:24,040
But still, it's not like I want to
be your new best friend or anything.

1119
01:17:24,379 --> 01:17:28,909
I mean I still hate you a lot, and
I pretty sure you hate me too right?

1120
01:17:29,513 --> 01:17:32,752
So why don't we stop pretending
or something we're not okay?

1121
01:17:33,040 --> 01:17:36,067
Let's shake on it from one hater to another.

1122
01:17:38,380 --> 01:17:41,503
You wrong, I don't hate you...

1123
01:17:41,780 --> 01:17:42,960
I.....I.....

1124
01:17:42,960 --> 01:17:44,707
I hate myself...

1125
01:17:44,840 --> 01:17:46,205
What did you say?

1126
01:17:46,532 --> 01:17:50,864
What did you say?

1127
01:17:52,360 --> 01:17:56,915
Well what are you gonna do? You can't say sorry again?

1128
01:17:57,580 --> 01:17:59,120
It has been five years,

1129
01:17:59,145 --> 01:18:04,239
and you haven't changed a bit. You still
have no intention of being real with me.

1130
01:18:09,580 --> 01:18:10,748
What do you think?

1131
01:18:12,347 --> 01:18:13,474
It's all...

1132
01:18:17,060 --> 01:18:18,055
all I want...

1133
01:18:19,552 --> 01:18:21,502
is for Shoko to like herself.

1134
01:18:30,675 --> 01:18:32,406
Are you sure with Naoka?

1135
01:18:32,460 --> 01:18:33,959
Yeah it was her.

1136
01:18:34,723 --> 01:18:37,747
Is there really a lot of bad blood between her and Shoko?

1137
01:18:37,953 --> 01:18:39,500
Why do you ask?

1138
01:18:40,233 --> 01:18:43,461
Miki said something serious went down at your old school.

1139
01:18:44,940 --> 01:18:49,580
Shoko's hearing is really bad. I
mean she can barely hear anything right?

1140
01:18:50,290 --> 01:18:51,025
Yeah.

1141
01:18:51,439 --> 01:18:55,944
It just occurred to me, maybe that's why
she kept getting bullied all the time you know?

1142
01:18:57,435 --> 01:18:59,865
You'd have to be a major douche bag

1143
01:19:00,166 --> 01:19:01,746
who bullies a deaf kid.

1144
01:19:02,133 --> 01:19:04,203
What's wrong with people right?

1145
01:19:04,513 --> 01:19:05,867
What are you saying!?

1146
01:19:05,960 --> 01:19:09,115
Wait! You think I'm spreading rumors
about what happened at elementary school?

1147
01:19:09,140 --> 01:19:11,715
Shush! will you keep it down?
The whole school can hear you.

1148
01:19:13,960 --> 01:19:17,055
I really wanted to believe that
you would actually change Shoya.

1149
01:19:17,102 --> 01:19:19,615
But you are still the same awful
person you were in elementary school.

1150
01:19:19,640 --> 01:19:20,285
Are you okay?

1151
01:19:20,310 --> 01:19:22,644
Can you just please calm down a second.

1152
01:19:23,320 --> 01:19:24,540
Hey guys what's going on.

1153
01:19:24,540 --> 01:19:26,668
Remember when I told you Shoko was bullied?

1154
01:19:26,761 --> 01:19:29,654
Well it was Shoko, he was the one who used to bully her.

1155
01:19:32,300 --> 01:19:36,060
How can you say that Miki?
Ya-sho would never do that.

1156
01:19:36,060 --> 01:19:37,916
Why I make up something like that.

1157
01:19:39,199 --> 01:19:41,388
But you used to make fun of her to Miki.

1158
01:19:41,600 --> 01:19:45,175
I never ever said anything horrible behind Shoko's back.

1159
01:19:45,200 --> 01:19:46,909
What you picked on Shoko?

1160
01:19:47,042 --> 01:19:50,468
Yeah, was him! He was the one
who made Shoko's life a living hell.

1161
01:19:52,617 --> 01:19:56,521
It was so awful I kept begging him to leave her alone.

1162
01:19:56,801 --> 01:19:59,027
But Shoya never listens to anyone.

1163
01:19:59,606 --> 01:20:01,046
I'm so scared of him.

1164
01:20:03,733 --> 01:20:05,335
Ya-sho?

1165
01:20:06,053 --> 01:20:07,413
What's wrong?

1166
01:20:07,846 --> 01:20:08,935
Sorry, Nagatsuka...

1167
01:20:08,960 --> 01:20:09,897
Are you OK?

1168
01:20:12,374 --> 01:20:13,474
Ya-sho!

1169
01:20:42,052 --> 01:20:44,987
Yeah, I hate me too...

1170
01:20:56,520 --> 01:20:58,092
Hey we're over here.

1171
01:20:58,117 --> 01:20:58,818
Hi!

1172
01:21:00,960 --> 01:21:02,120
Is something wrong?

1173
01:21:03,820 --> 01:21:05,392
Oh no, not really.

1174
01:21:06,540 --> 01:21:07,203
It's nothing...

1175
01:21:07,253 --> 01:21:07,725
Huh?

1176
01:21:09,373 --> 01:21:11,488
There he is. My main man.

1177
01:21:11,700 --> 01:21:13,612
I brought your backpack for you!

1178
01:21:13,710 --> 01:21:14,735
Hey guys.

1179
01:21:14,845 --> 01:21:15,827
Naoka...?

1180
01:21:16,866 --> 01:21:18,192
...I asked her to come.

1181
01:21:22,447 --> 01:21:24,313
I'm sorry about what happened.

1182
01:21:25,260 --> 01:21:29,676
But well you were the one who
started causing all that trouble.

1183
01:21:30,340 --> 01:21:37,288
Nothing is Satoshi said I should go ahead and forgive you
since you've been trying to make things right with Shoko.

1184
01:21:38,133 --> 01:21:39,526
Are you kidding me?

1185
01:21:39,880 --> 01:21:42,217
This is wrong on so many levels.

1186
01:21:42,313 --> 01:21:46,078
You can't blame everything that
happened on Shoya. We were all guilty.

1187
01:21:47,280 --> 01:21:48,126
We?

1188
01:21:48,823 --> 01:21:50,130
But no, that isn't true.

1189
01:21:50,130 --> 01:21:51,168
What's not?

1190
01:21:52,135 --> 01:21:56,855
I never made fun of Shoko. Did anything to
bully her the way the rest of you guys did.

1191
01:21:57,296 --> 01:21:58,971
Don't lump me in with you.

1192
01:22:00,340 --> 01:22:01,415
Naoka...

1193
01:22:02,417 --> 01:22:03,930
Hmmm...

1194
01:22:05,406 --> 01:22:08,956
You're right. You and I are completely different.

1195
01:22:09,100 --> 01:22:11,648
You just that back and laughed along with everyone else.

1196
01:22:11,940 --> 01:22:12,915
It's not!

1197
01:22:13,080 --> 01:22:14,688
Just asked Miyoko!

1198
01:22:15,213 --> 01:22:16,238
What? Me!?

1199
01:22:16,630 --> 01:22:19,790
Naoka used to talk about you
behind your back all the time too.

1200
01:22:19,790 --> 01:22:21,980
I just said what everyone else was thinking.

1201
01:22:23,587 --> 01:22:26,013
Well Miyoko, wanna weigh in?

1202
01:22:27,934 --> 01:22:29,528
To be completely honest...

1203
01:22:29,912 --> 01:22:30,652
back then I was...

1204
01:22:31,280 --> 01:22:33,660
I was scared of both of you.

1205
01:22:33,660 --> 01:22:35,660
What!? Whose side are you are anyway!?

1206
01:22:35,660 --> 01:22:37,130
I'm not on anyone's side!

1207
01:22:37,130 --> 01:22:38,270
Just stop.

1208
01:22:40,000 --> 01:22:43,010
It's my fault okay. It's all my fault.

1209
01:22:44,779 --> 01:22:46,538
I can't stand martyrs..

1210
01:22:49,120 --> 01:22:50,370
That's enough Naoka.

1211
01:22:51,160 --> 01:22:53,694
Stop trying to drag everybody else down here level.

1212
01:22:53,920 --> 01:22:55,580
That was harsh! You didn't have to put...

1213
01:22:55,580 --> 01:22:56,935
Oh, please, Miyoko.

1214
01:22:57,208 --> 01:23:00,234
We all know that you just run
away when other things get intense.

1215
01:23:01,015 --> 01:23:02,940
Shoya, what's gotten into you...

1216
01:23:02,940 --> 01:23:06,208
God will you just stop talking?

1217
01:23:06,300 --> 01:23:09,003
You really love the sound of your own voice don't you?

1218
01:23:10,060 --> 01:23:11,198
Listen man,

1219
01:23:11,280 --> 01:23:13,608
No matter what anyone says I've got your back.

1220
01:23:13,840 --> 01:23:18,681
I don't care what you just
back off. You hardly know me.

1221
01:23:18,720 --> 01:23:21,707
I can't take this anymore.
I'm not staying here.

1222
01:23:22,165 --> 01:23:23,366
It's okay.

1223
01:23:23,860 --> 01:23:24,660
You don't mean it.

1224
01:23:25,281 --> 01:23:27,356
But I'm gonna give you some space.

1225
01:23:29,966 --> 01:23:30,952
Hey Shoko,

1226
01:23:32,444 --> 01:23:33,052
later.

1227
01:23:39,640 --> 01:23:41,043
I'm sorry, Shoya.

1228
01:23:42,560 --> 01:23:45,282
I never should have agreed to come here to begin with.

1229
01:23:48,131 --> 01:23:51,006
It's not cool. We're way to harsh.

1230
01:23:52,500 --> 01:23:55,392
What do you know? You're not
even really part of our group.

1231
01:23:56,326 --> 01:23:58,012
I thought we were friends.

1232
01:24:11,327 --> 01:24:12,320
Almost forgot...

1233
01:24:13,495 --> 01:24:15,295
So starting next week,

1234
01:24:15,646 --> 01:24:17,070
it's summer vacation.

1235
01:24:18,013 --> 01:24:19,934
Do you want to go somewhere special?

1236
01:24:38,750 --> 01:24:39,952
Yuzu.

1237
01:24:41,233 --> 01:24:44,447
You're going to ruin your eyes
reading in the dark like that.

1238
01:24:50,520 --> 01:24:51,143
Here.

1239
01:24:58,232 --> 01:25:01,992
You spend so much time worried about your big sister.

1240
01:25:04,360 --> 01:25:07,408
Now I'm starting to worry about you. Sweetie.

1241
01:25:08,040 --> 01:25:10,880
You get so caught up in Shoko's life

1242
01:25:10,880 --> 01:25:13,911
that you never leave any time for yourself.

1243
01:25:13,940 --> 01:25:16,360
I could say the same thing about you granny!

1244
01:25:16,360 --> 01:25:20,667
Instead of going to the senior center
all you do is study sign language.

1245
01:25:20,900 --> 01:25:24,526
That's something I'm doing for
myself so that doesn't really count.

1246
01:25:24,740 --> 01:25:28,576
What a coincidence. Because I'm
doing all these things for myself too.

1247
01:25:29,853 --> 01:25:30,761
Really?

1248
01:25:34,480 --> 01:25:36,484
You are such a good kid.

1249
01:25:36,995 --> 01:25:37,977
You think so?

1250
01:25:38,320 --> 01:25:40,760
Mom chews me out on a daily basis,

1251
01:25:40,812 --> 01:25:43,171
and I haven't gone to school in like... weeks.

1252
01:25:43,640 --> 01:25:46,399
Yes, sweetie. But you've got a heart of gold.

1253
01:25:46,760 --> 01:25:48,954
Shoko is no slouchy either.

1254
01:25:50,920 --> 01:25:53,668
I've got some mighty fine grandchildren.

1255
01:25:58,180 --> 01:26:00,166
Have one of the Manju too?

1256
01:26:00,352 --> 01:26:01,452
You've got it!

1257
01:26:16,427 --> 01:26:17,380
Granny...

1258
01:26:30,420 --> 01:26:32,196
Hey there, Shoko.

1259
01:26:32,580 --> 01:26:35,969
So today, I was able to score some really great bread.

1260
01:26:36,004 --> 01:26:39,303
See! It's awesome, like you're awesome.

1261
01:26:41,210 --> 01:26:45,786
Oh like really great bread is
awesome, This loaf here is just like you.

1262
01:26:47,070 --> 01:26:48,747
That makes no sense.

1263
01:26:49,640 --> 01:26:50,247
Huh...?

1264
01:26:52,210 --> 01:26:53,902
I wonder if she's coming today?

1265
01:26:57,460 --> 01:26:58,153
I guess not...

1266
01:26:59,140 --> 01:27:01,517
Is your stomach bothering you?

1267
01:27:02,220 --> 01:27:03,469
Is it not too personal?

1268
01:27:13,020 --> 01:27:15,205
Hey, Yuzu???

1269
01:27:29,410 --> 01:27:30,397
I should go...

1270
01:27:30,580 --> 01:27:31,550
Shoya!

1271
01:27:32,250 --> 01:27:32,967
Hey there!

1272
01:27:33,293 --> 01:27:34,623
What the heck are you wearing?

1273
01:27:34,822 --> 01:27:37,160
What's it look like. My uniform.

1274
01:27:37,242 --> 01:27:38,841
What do you think? You like?

1275
01:27:38,961 --> 01:27:40,049
Why are you wearing it?

1276
01:27:40,074 --> 01:27:40,987
For school.

1277
01:27:43,440 --> 01:27:44,939
But we're on summer break right now.

1278
01:27:44,964 --> 01:27:45,504
Ehh...

1279
01:27:46,856 --> 01:27:48,676
So what's really going on?

1280
01:27:51,060 --> 01:27:52,919
Nothing is going on I swear.

1281
01:27:53,075 --> 01:27:55,699
If anyone asks, tell him cosplay!

1282
01:27:56,120 --> 01:27:56,765
Huh.

1283
01:27:58,210 --> 01:28:00,944
That was from my sister so I better take off.

1284
01:28:01,024 --> 01:28:02,390
Where to? I'll walk you there.

1285
01:28:02,597 --> 01:28:03,703
No. It's fine.

1286
01:28:03,859 --> 01:28:04,822
You sure you're okay?

1287
01:28:05,130 --> 01:28:06,742
Yeah, everything is cool.

1288
01:28:07,292 --> 01:28:09,039
Then why you were crying just now.

1289
01:28:09,738 --> 01:28:10,372
Come on!

1290
01:28:13,284 --> 01:28:16,244
This actually doesn't have anything to do with you.

1291
01:28:16,820 --> 01:28:17,795
Sure it does...

1292
01:28:18,740 --> 01:28:20,280
At least, I think so.

1293
01:28:20,866 --> 01:28:21,473
Why?

1294
01:28:22,259 --> 01:28:24,059
I'm just worried about you okay.

1295
01:28:26,219 --> 01:28:29,196
I don't believe it you sound just like my grandma.

1296
01:28:31,052 --> 01:28:33,639
All right if you wanna come then come.

1297
01:28:37,022 --> 01:28:38,162
This is it.

1298
01:28:38,495 --> 01:28:41,832
Thanks for walking me. I appreciate it.

1299
01:28:42,011 --> 01:28:44,340
<i>"Funeral service for Ito Nishimiya"</i>

1300
01:28:44,466 --> 01:28:45,713
See you.

1301
01:28:51,586 --> 01:28:53,040
Good lucky, Yuzuru!

1302
01:28:56,800 --> 01:28:58,765
Shoya. Wait.

1303
01:29:01,900 --> 01:29:03,882
Truth is... I am scared.

1304
01:30:03,240 --> 01:30:05,899
<i>"How about hanging out
somewhere tomorrow?"</i>

1305
01:30:59,100 --> 01:31:00,750
Wow, that's cool!

1306
01:31:03,227 --> 01:31:05,693
Come on, Shoko. Let's go check it out.

1307
01:31:08,000 --> 01:31:08,723
Huh?

1308
01:31:14,920 --> 01:31:16,470
Shoko?

1309
01:31:25,069 --> 01:31:26,223
I'm fine really.

1310
01:31:28,653 --> 01:31:30,533
Why are you apologizing?

1311
01:31:36,790 --> 01:31:38,634
That's totally not true!

1312
01:31:39,000 --> 01:31:41,483
Hey, are you busy tomorrow?

1313
01:31:41,940 --> 01:31:43,374
Let's hang out tomorrow, too!

1314
01:31:47,900 --> 01:31:48,818
Shoko said...

1315
01:31:49,116 --> 01:31:51,484
that I'll be miserable whenever I'm with her.

1316
01:31:54,146 --> 01:31:56,056
But I'm the one who made her unhappy.

1317
01:31:57,153 --> 01:31:58,104
It was me...

1318
01:32:08,360 --> 01:32:12,129
I want to see the sea,

1319
01:32:13,400 --> 01:32:17,620
I want to have somemone love me,

1320
01:32:18,793 --> 01:32:22,004
even monsters feel

1321
01:32:23,000 --> 01:32:24,884
feel there are...

1322
01:32:27,600 --> 01:32:30,062
There's no going back to the way things were...

1323
01:32:35,300 --> 01:32:39,135
Hey! Shoko. Cool! I see Yuzuru
is going to get along with us.

1324
01:32:39,160 --> 01:32:40,310
Let's check outa movie!

1325
01:32:40,543 --> 01:32:43,416
Ha ha ha, this is hilarious.

