01:32:43,600 --> 01:32:45,960
Hey greetings classmates!

1327
01:32:46,040 --> 01:32:49,625
I gotta say this has been the best summer break ever.

1328
01:32:49,680 --> 01:32:50,791
Just ask Yuzuru?

1329
01:32:50,816 --> 01:32:51,746
Whatever...

1330
01:32:51,820 --> 01:32:54,472
Seriously, we're having an absolute blast.

1331
01:32:54,552 --> 01:32:55,565
What about tomorrow.

1332
01:32:55,874 --> 01:32:59,060
We should go somewhere fun.
Any ideas? Where we should go?

1333
01:32:59,126 --> 01:33:02,012
Sorry, but we already have plans for tomorrow.

1334
01:33:02,445 --> 01:33:03,056
Huh?

1335
01:33:04,820 --> 01:33:07,020
Hah? No way. Are you insane?

1336
01:33:07,020 --> 01:33:07,766
Wants to make what?

1337
01:33:07,880 --> 01:33:09,066
You sure it's okay?

1338
01:33:09,186 --> 01:33:11,632
I feel like I really shouldn't be here.

1339
01:33:11,720 --> 01:33:13,940
Your mission should you choose to accept?

1340
01:33:13,940 --> 01:33:17,126
It is to assist us in baking our mother's birthday cake.

1341
01:33:17,439 --> 01:33:19,245
Are you absolutely sure?

1342
01:33:19,695 --> 01:33:20,873
I don't want to get hit again.

1343
01:33:20,898 --> 01:33:23,650
She won't hit you. She'll probably kill you this time.

1344
01:33:23,675 --> 01:33:24,510
For real?

1345
01:33:25,660 --> 01:33:28,391
Oh that looks amazing!

1346
01:33:30,360 --> 01:33:31,630
Why is he here?

1347
01:33:31,720 --> 01:33:33,554
What's that boy doing our kitchen?

1348
01:33:33,620 --> 01:33:35,120
I want an explanation right now.

1349
01:33:35,120 --> 01:33:40,339
Come on, mom, don't be like that. It's a
party! We're supposed to be celebrating.

1350
01:33:40,386 --> 01:33:41,136
Yuzuru.

1351
01:33:41,170 --> 01:33:42,384
You look great!

1352
01:33:43,697 --> 01:33:44,670
Eh...

1353
01:33:51,340 --> 01:33:54,539
You lucked out, looks like mom isn't gonna kill you.

1354
01:33:55,740 --> 01:33:57,460
I declare a victory.

1355
01:33:57,591 --> 01:33:59,453
Speaking of winning,

1356
01:33:59,653 --> 01:34:03,474
I submitted some of your photography
to the local contest Yuzuru.

1357
01:34:03,521 --> 01:34:04,028
Huh?

1358
01:34:04,400 --> 01:34:05,160
You what?

1359
01:34:05,160 --> 01:34:06,840
It was actually your sister's idea.

1360
01:34:10,920 --> 01:34:13,700
What? But I'm no good. I'm just messing around.

1361
01:34:13,700 --> 01:34:15,399
Oh, come on, that's not true.

1362
01:34:15,992 --> 01:34:18,754
Why would you do this to me.

1363
01:34:19,920 --> 01:34:23,959
Before I forget, next Tuesday you're coming
to see the fireworks with us sitll right?

1364
01:34:26,300 --> 01:34:27,495
I don't have to.

1365
01:34:27,733 --> 01:34:29,397
You're totally coming...

1366
01:34:41,620 --> 01:34:43,489
Is here okay?

1367
01:34:43,560 --> 01:34:44,595
Yeah, this is good.

1368
01:35:13,820 --> 01:35:15,957
Well, perfect time to go buy snacks.

1369
01:35:16,040 --> 01:35:17,183
Want to come on?

1370
01:35:29,340 --> 01:35:30,441
Oh, thank you.

1371
01:35:32,455 --> 01:35:34,636
Thanks for inviting me over the other day too.

1372
01:35:35,009 --> 01:35:36,056
Your mom...

1373
01:35:36,897 --> 01:35:38,599
You really think she was happy?

1374
01:35:39,607 --> 01:35:40,794
I couldn't tell...

1375
01:35:42,193 --> 01:35:43,642
Speaking of which...

1376
01:35:43,900 --> 01:35:45,748
I don't know when your birthday is.

1377
01:35:47,290 --> 01:35:50,142
Your birthday was June 7th.

1378
01:35:50,415 --> 01:35:53,521
Oh no I missed it. That's too bad.

1379
01:35:53,780 --> 01:35:55,932
I can't believe you're already 18.

1380
01:35:56,324 --> 01:35:58,650
Next year, we'll celebrate together.

1381
01:35:59,052 --> 01:36:00,565
We'll throw a big party.

1382
01:36:01,180 --> 01:36:03,311
I made it sound like we're together.

1383
01:36:06,560 --> 01:36:07,177
Oh.

1384
01:36:27,460 --> 01:36:28,462
I get now.

1385
01:36:28,555 --> 01:36:29,946
That makes perfect sense.

1386
01:36:31,386 --> 01:36:32,896
That's why you closed your eyes.

1387
01:36:35,064 --> 01:36:36,945
Oh, where are you going?

1388
01:36:40,707 --> 01:36:44,422
What? Why now? The fireworks only just started.

1389
01:36:47,140 --> 01:36:48,465
To go study...

1390
01:36:49,946 --> 01:36:50,697
Okay.

1391
01:36:51,220 --> 01:36:53,422
Hey wait up I'll walk you home.

1392
01:36:54,840 --> 01:36:56,021
But why...

1393
01:37:02,600 --> 01:37:04,180
Oh well

1394
01:37:04,180 --> 01:37:05,118
See you later.

1395
01:37:15,600 --> 01:37:18,095
Hey what happened to Shoko?

1396
01:37:19,020 --> 01:37:21,392
Oh, I forgot my camera.

1397
01:37:21,440 --> 01:37:23,731
Would you mind going back to our place to get it?

1398
01:37:36,580 --> 01:37:38,298
I'm coming in...

1399
01:37:38,717 --> 01:37:40,077
Oh, it's dark.

1400
01:37:40,379 --> 01:37:41,739
Shoko, you here?

1401
01:37:41,880 --> 01:37:43,164
It's me, Shoya.

1402
01:37:44,204 --> 01:37:45,184
There it is.

1403
01:37:46,399 --> 01:37:49,079
Shouldn't I make sure it's fully charged...?

1404
01:37:49,767 --> 01:37:52,289
Huh? Oh, you see the fireworks from here.

1405
01:37:54,226 --> 01:37:55,881
So that's where she is.

1406
01:37:58,100 --> 01:37:58,829
She...

1407
01:37:59,440 --> 01:38:00,589
Hey...

1408
01:38:01,246 --> 01:38:02,816
Wait, wait! Wait a second!

1409
01:38:03,480 --> 01:38:04,495
What is she doing?!

1410
01:38:04,854 --> 01:38:05,881
Hey, Shoko?

1411
01:38:10,566 --> 01:38:11,491
Shoko...!?

1412
01:38:13,180 --> 01:38:14,245
Huh!

1413
01:38:22,820 --> 01:38:23,700
Don't do it!

1414
01:38:23,700 --> 01:38:25,100
Ah! Ouch!

1415
01:38:30,371 --> 01:38:31,404
Please no...!

1416
01:38:34,167 --> 01:38:35,852
Shoko!

1417
01:39:07,340 --> 01:39:10,015
You have to hold on to the railing.

1418
01:39:11,059 --> 01:39:11,754
Please, God...

1419
01:39:12,421 --> 01:39:17,087
Give me one more ounce of strength... I
won't run away from my problem anymore.

1420
01:39:18,053 --> 01:39:20,415
Just through this one thing for me please.

1421
01:39:21,380 --> 01:39:24,918
Starting tomorrow... I'll look everyone in the eye.

1422
01:39:26,440 --> 01:39:30,336
Starting tomorrow... I'll listen when people speak to me.

1423
01:39:31,440 --> 01:39:34,617
Starting tomorrow... I'll be better.

1424
01:39:34,919 --> 01:39:36,919
Shoko...

1425
01:39:39,682 --> 01:39:43,092
There it is the scar I gave her all those years ago.

1426
01:39:43,420 --> 01:39:45,647
Did I ever even apologize for that

1427
01:39:46,790 --> 01:39:47,702
I'm sorry.

1428
01:39:48,340 --> 01:39:50,117
Sorry for everything Shoko.

1429
01:39:50,806 --> 01:39:52,025
Are you still mad at me?

1430
01:39:52,906 --> 01:39:54,733
Huh, I'm so dumb.

1431
01:39:55,700 --> 01:39:58,141
I should have asked her what she really thinks of me.

1432
01:39:58,906 --> 01:40:00,307
But now I don't know if.

1433
01:40:01,800 --> 01:40:04,826
By the way, Shoko. I think that I might...

1434
01:40:17,880 --> 01:40:19,026
He there Sho,

1435
01:40:19,100 --> 01:40:22,398
your sister whipped you up some of her famous pancake.

1436
01:40:22,500 --> 01:40:25,249
I'm going to watch the fireworks!

1437
01:40:37,120 --> 01:40:38,151
It's cold...

1438
01:40:39,180 --> 01:40:40,522
It's warm...

1439
01:41:06,900 --> 01:41:08,457
Mrs Ishida.

1440
01:41:08,786 --> 01:41:10,184
What are you doing here?

1441
01:41:11,040 --> 01:41:12,492
I'm glad I caught you.

1442
01:41:12,680 --> 01:41:15,789
I tried calling the so long but it was closed.

1443
01:41:15,980 --> 01:41:18,455
I just wanted to know about Shoya...

1444
01:41:18,520 --> 01:41:20,663
Well he's doing a lot better.

1445
01:41:20,745 --> 01:41:22,536
They moved him out of the ICU.

1446
01:41:22,920 --> 01:41:25,711
I was going to his new room. Do you want to come with me?

1447
01:41:26,813 --> 01:41:28,005
Do you know if Shoya...

1448
01:41:28,080 --> 01:41:29,165
Mrs Ishita...

1449
01:41:29,973 --> 01:41:31,553
Mrs Nishimiya...

1450
01:41:32,670 --> 01:41:35,483
I'm very sorry for all the trouble Shoya has caused.

1451
01:41:35,540 --> 01:41:38,736
I know what he did in the past
is unforgivable. But I want you...

1452
01:41:39,840 --> 01:41:41,062
Please forgive me.

1453
01:41:42,060 --> 01:41:44,725
What are you doing? Oh get up...

1454
01:41:45,000 --> 01:41:46,700
I'm sure Shoya must have done something...

1455
01:41:46,725 --> 01:41:47,610
Mrs Ishida,

1456
01:41:47,677 --> 01:41:51,229
Shoya was trying to save my stupid sister.

1457
01:41:51,455 --> 01:41:56,675
If I do better... she wouldn't have...

1458
01:41:56,700 --> 01:41:58,870
I'm so sorry.

1459
01:41:58,954 --> 01:42:00,787
Please don't.

1460
01:42:01,460 --> 01:42:03,604
Come on, both you. Please get up.

1461
01:42:03,710 --> 01:42:06,343
I'm just glad that Shoko was okay.

1462
01:42:06,710 --> 01:42:08,538
And you too Yuzuru...

1463
01:42:09,892 --> 01:42:10,953
So please get up...

1464
01:42:12,976 --> 01:42:16,362
Why is Shoya lying in a hospital bed instead of you?

1465
01:42:16,549 --> 01:42:19,481
Don't you dare try to play the victim.

1466
01:42:21,166 --> 01:42:22,572
Say something!

1467
01:42:22,860 --> 01:42:26,940
What? You finally come back for all
the problems you created for everyone.

1468
01:42:26,940 --> 01:42:28,803
So you thought you would kill yourself.

1469
01:42:28,840 --> 01:42:32,322
And now all you can say
is "I'm sorry"? Is that it?

1470
01:42:32,380 --> 01:42:34,442
Well that's not going to cut it anymore.

1471
01:42:34,640 --> 01:42:35,954
Who do you think you are, huh?

1472
01:42:36,100 --> 01:42:38,587
You're a loser, a deaf loser.

1473
01:42:38,620 --> 01:42:40,297
You sit there in your own little world

1474
01:42:40,340 --> 01:42:42,210
and ignore everyone else around you.

1475
01:42:42,210 --> 01:42:44,396
You're the most selfish person I know.

1476
01:42:49,126 --> 01:42:51,112
Hey who the hell are you?

1477
01:42:55,975 --> 01:42:58,147
You must be the little loser's mother!

1478
01:42:58,281 --> 01:43:02,760
If you can't keep your kid in line
then do us all a favor and stop breathing.

1479
01:43:02,785 --> 01:43:04,169
What are you two doing?

1480
01:43:04,898 --> 01:43:06,023
That's enough.

1481
01:43:09,200 --> 01:43:10,615
I said that's enough.

1482
01:43:10,815 --> 01:43:14,763
Stop it. What is wrong with the both of you?

1483
01:43:25,860 --> 01:43:28,457
Shoko, are you okay?

1484
01:43:36,427 --> 01:43:37,878
I am sorry.

1485
01:43:43,616 --> 01:43:45,216
I am so sorry.

1486
01:43:50,993 --> 01:43:52,967
That's all my fault.

1487
01:44:05,260 --> 01:44:06,347
What are you doing?

1488
01:44:07,516 --> 01:44:10,091
I thought if she saw what death looked like,

1489
01:44:10,126 --> 01:44:12,966
she'd stop saying she wanted to kill herself.

1490
01:44:17,380 --> 01:44:21,061
I didn't know what else to do...

1491
01:45:08,260 --> 01:45:09,684
I can't open it.

1492
01:45:09,740 --> 01:45:11,357
Someone is holding it.

1493
01:45:11,420 --> 01:45:13,585
Oh I didn't notice you there Shoko.

1494
01:45:13,680 --> 01:45:16,876
Are you thirsty? How about I buy you a drink.

1495
01:45:17,100 --> 01:45:18,580
<i>"Hospital rooms
400-417"</i>

1496
01:45:18,624 --> 01:45:21,360
I heard what happened with you and Ya-sho.

1497
01:45:23,220 --> 01:45:26,125
<i>"I destroyed what Ishida-kun
created working so hard."</i>

1498
01:45:26,219 --> 01:45:28,845
Does this have to do with that stuff on the bridge?

1499
01:45:30,042 --> 01:45:34,290
Ya-sho was kind and open-hearted
enough to accept a guy like me.

1500
01:45:34,420 --> 01:45:39,354
For the first time, I know what it
feels like to have a true friend.

1501
01:45:43,733 --> 01:45:46,473
Ya-sho is my best friend in the whole world.

1502
01:45:46,560 --> 01:45:48,993
So I know he'll wake up. He just has to...

1503
01:45:57,031 --> 01:46:00,795
<i>"I want to fix what I destroyed."</i>

1504
01:46:02,446 --> 01:46:03,179
Oh...

1505
01:46:06,207 --> 01:46:09,699
You wanted to die because you were
suffering? What were you thinking!

1506
01:46:09,779 --> 01:46:11,920
Just calm down, everybody is staring.

1507
01:46:11,920 --> 01:46:16,464
I don't care about who's listening. I
have to be loud in order for Shoko to hear me.

1508
01:46:20,055 --> 01:46:22,230
We were all so worried about you.

1509
01:46:22,340 --> 01:46:26,643
I know life can be hard sometimes.
It's like that for everyone.

1510
01:46:27,273 --> 01:46:33,385
Thing is you have to accept the bad parts of
yourself with the bad and just move forward.

1511
01:46:37,480 --> 01:46:39,390
I am really glad you're okay.

1512
01:46:40,980 --> 01:46:42,808
<i>"I want to fix what I destroyed."</i>

1513
01:46:42,833 --> 01:46:43,653
I see,

1514
01:46:43,913 --> 01:46:46,219
So you went to see everyone then.

1515
01:46:46,886 --> 01:46:48,085
That's awesome...

1516
01:46:50,200 --> 01:46:53,460
But I'm not as brave as you.

1517
01:46:53,560 --> 01:46:56,599
Even if Sharia does wake up from his coma.

1518
01:46:56,836 --> 01:47:00,229
I think I'd be too ashamed to face him.

1519
01:47:00,715 --> 01:47:03,497
Because he's right, I haven't changed one bit.

1520
01:47:03,700 --> 01:47:06,192
You needed help and I still wasn't there for you.

1521
01:47:06,491 --> 01:47:08,431
I'm the same coward as I've always been.

1522
01:47:09,682 --> 01:47:12,272
You can change from now.

1523
01:47:13,710 --> 01:47:15,510
It is not too late.

1524
01:47:18,771 --> 01:47:21,388
I'm really glad you came to see me, Sho.

1525
01:48:02,360 --> 01:48:06,880
Hey, stop it! Cut it out!

1526
01:48:15,640 --> 01:48:16,850
<i>"Nishimiya"</i>

1527
01:48:17,807 --> 01:48:19,660
<i>"I found you..."</i>

1528
01:48:20,630 --> 01:48:23,680
<i>"Are you doing well?"</i>

1529
01:48:24,750 --> 01:48:25,685
<i>"Somewhat?"</i>

1530
01:48:26,420 --> 01:48:28,620
<i>"Strange, isn't it?"</i>

1531
01:48:29,400 --> 01:48:30,074
<i>"I think..."</i>

1532
01:48:30,661 --> 01:48:32,600
<i>"I am going to die."</i>

1533
01:48:33,281 --> 01:48:34,241
<i>"Oh..."</i>

1534
01:48:35,000 --> 01:48:37,440
<i>"Tuesday is almost over."</i>

1535
01:48:38,365 --> 01:48:39,900
<i>"Farewell,"</i>

1536
01:48:40,178 --> 01:48:41,098
<i>"Nishimiya..."</i>

1537
01:49:44,881 --> 01:49:45,928
No! Shoko!

1538
01:49:49,460 --> 01:49:50,638
What's all this?

1539
01:49:51,160 --> 01:49:52,033
Mom!

1540
01:49:52,320 --> 01:49:54,612
Hello? What's going on?

1541
01:50:02,320 --> 01:50:03,327
Shoko?

1542
01:50:05,106 --> 01:50:06,373
Oh was there?

1543
01:50:16,840 --> 01:50:17,983
She is here.

1544
01:50:22,980 --> 01:50:23,977
I am so sorry.

1545
01:50:39,020 --> 01:50:39,656
Yo!

1546
01:51:13,780 --> 01:51:18,211
Aha ha ha.

1547
01:51:22,393 --> 01:51:24,005
Hey! Why are you crying?

1548
01:51:32,360 --> 01:51:33,454
I'm really glad

1549
01:51:35,011 --> 01:51:35,998
you are okay.

1550
01:51:39,840 --> 01:51:41,096
Don't worry, Shoko.

1551
01:51:41,680 --> 01:51:44,709
I am fine now. I promise...

1552
01:51:45,880 --> 01:51:47,315
...more or less.

1553
01:51:48,996 --> 01:51:51,901
So stop looking so gloomy, okay?

1554
01:51:52,930 --> 01:51:53,753
Oh yeah...

1555
01:51:57,679 --> 01:51:58,872
I want to tell you...

1556
01:52:01,053 --> 01:52:02,326
that I'm really sorry.

1557
01:52:03,100 --> 01:52:07,298
I never apologized for all the
stuff I did to you when we were kids...

1558
01:52:08,566 --> 01:52:11,497
...or any of the other stuff afterwards either.

1559
01:52:12,486 --> 01:52:13,598
So I'm sorry...

1560
01:52:15,633 --> 01:52:16,773
But the thing is...

1561
01:52:17,195 --> 01:52:18,900
Even though you were going through a lot...

1562
01:52:18,900 --> 01:52:24,449
I was being selfish and focused
on myself more than anything.

1563
01:52:24,713 --> 01:52:27,846
I wanted to have a conversation with you.

1564
01:52:29,760 --> 01:52:32,660
I wasn't trying to hurt you...

1565
01:52:34,215 --> 01:52:35,234
but I must have.

1566
01:52:35,533 --> 01:52:39,147
Because I made you feel so bad about yourself.

1567
01:52:39,695 --> 01:52:42,181
Then you decided to go and do the unthinkable.

1568
01:52:42,630 --> 01:52:45,009
No, you are wrong.

1569
01:52:45,034 --> 01:52:46,942
It because I couldn't change.

1570
01:52:47,048 --> 01:52:48,830
And that's why you fell.

1571
01:52:49,000 --> 01:52:50,196
It's me.

1572
01:52:50,720 --> 01:52:53,860
Everything is all my fault.

1573
01:52:54,580 --> 01:52:58,185
So I thought should I just disappear...

1574
01:52:58,210 --> 01:53:00,187
I am so selfish...

1575
01:53:02,720 --> 01:53:03,940
I am sorry.

1576
01:53:03,940 --> 01:53:06,541
Please, that's not true. Don't cry.

1577
01:53:09,799 --> 01:53:13,023
Shoko. Look at me.

1578
01:53:17,480 --> 01:53:19,910
Did you know we were talking a little while ago...

1579
01:53:20,913 --> 01:53:21,963
I was dreaming

1580
01:53:22,760 --> 01:53:26,476
and in this dream I was ready
to just give up on everything.

1581
01:53:27,319 --> 01:53:28,279
But I was wrong.

1582
01:53:29,060 --> 01:53:34,290
To be honest, I've thought about
ending things just like you did.

1583
01:53:35,480 --> 01:53:37,284
But then, I realized something,

1584
01:53:38,320 --> 01:53:41,512
Even though certain things can
make life difficult sometimes.

1585
01:53:42,729 --> 01:53:45,189
that doesn't mean they are worth and dying over.

1586
01:53:46,880 --> 01:53:50,154
I want to apologize and make sure I do it right.

1587
01:53:52,582 --> 01:53:53,318
Shoko.

1588
01:53:54,442 --> 01:53:56,367
I need some help from you.

1589
01:54:00,340 --> 01:54:01,482
I was hoping

1590
01:54:02,360 --> 01:54:03,728
that maybe you could

1591
01:54:04,880 --> 01:54:06,247
teach me how to live.

1592
01:54:14,710 --> 01:54:15,979
Please Shoko.

1593
01:54:37,780 --> 01:54:38,507
Oh God.

1594
01:54:40,540 --> 01:54:42,822
That's the creepiest thing I've ever said in my life.

1595
01:54:42,980 --> 01:54:45,712
Oh I'm so sorry... just never mind.

1596
01:54:46,040 --> 01:54:48,534
Forget everything I said okay? I didn't mean it.

1597
01:55:12,088 --> 01:55:14,814
You have arrived at your destination.

1598
01:55:15,361 --> 01:55:19,080
Hey there Maria become quite the
