1599
01:55:19,260 --> 01:55:20,433
They're looking good!

1600
01:55:21,580 --> 01:55:25,820
Sho-Sho!? You die? You die?

1601
01:55:25,820 --> 01:55:28,960
That's right Maria. Oh ur Sho came back from dead.

1602
01:55:28,960 --> 01:55:31,040
Don't listen to grandma, that wasn't really dead.

1603
01:55:31,283 --> 01:55:31,920
Hey look!

1604
01:55:32,118 --> 01:55:33,566
Isn't that Naoka?

1605
01:55:35,077 --> 01:55:38,834
You know she was by your side
the entire time you were in a coma.

1606
01:55:39,164 --> 01:55:40,720
You really should thank her.

1607
01:55:43,360 --> 01:55:45,412
My mom said you came to the hospital...

1608
01:55:45,785 --> 01:55:48,604
Listen I really suck at life sometimes...

1609
01:55:49,146 --> 01:55:51,597
Especially when it comes to stuff like this.

1610
01:55:52,326 --> 01:55:56,171
I just... I just can't bring myself to like Shoko.

1611
01:55:57,133 --> 01:55:58,768
Probably gonna regret this.

1612
01:55:59,381 --> 01:56:01,632
Remember when you fell in the river?

1613
01:56:01,898 --> 01:56:06,818
It was Kazuki and the guys who pulled
you out and he told me not to tell you.

1614
01:56:06,872 --> 01:56:07,497
But...

1615
01:56:08,480 --> 01:56:12,425
anyway welcome back.

1616
01:56:12,840 --> 01:56:14,526
Well I'm gonna take off.

1617
01:56:15,800 --> 01:56:16,973
Thanks Naoka.

1618
01:56:26,393 --> 01:56:29,310
I don't know, don't you think it's a little short?

1619
01:56:29,335 --> 01:56:31,948
No, no, it looks much cuter like this!

1620
01:56:31,981 --> 01:56:33,407
Oh your home Shoya.

1621
01:56:33,895 --> 01:56:35,295
Oh, hi Shoya.

1622
01:56:35,320 --> 01:56:36,513
Mrs Nishimiya.

1623
01:56:38,166 --> 01:56:40,146
Wait a minute. Yes?

1624
01:56:41,380 --> 01:56:42,412
I'm really sorry.

1625
01:56:42,626 --> 01:56:44,791
Yeah, me too.

1626
01:56:44,960 --> 01:56:47,540
No matter what my son always bounces our right back.

1627
01:56:47,540 --> 01:56:50,012
See you later mom I'm heading
out to pick up Maria now.

1628
01:56:50,177 --> 01:56:51,025
Okay!

1629
01:56:51,340 --> 01:56:51,851
Who's that?

1630
01:56:51,876 --> 01:56:54,725
He is my son-in-law. He's back from being deployed.

1631
01:56:54,805 --> 01:56:58,211
Oh Shoya, Yuzuru is waiting for you upstairs.

1632
01:56:58,286 --> 01:57:00,011
Give her the Jello that's in the fridge.

1633
01:57:01,560 --> 01:57:02,014
Yo.

1634
01:57:02,060 --> 01:57:03,048
Wow.

1635
01:57:03,540 --> 01:57:05,654
New threads? It looks good on you.

1636
01:57:05,840 --> 01:57:07,247
Check it out. I won.

1637
01:57:07,891 --> 01:57:10,280
Oh wow! No kidding, impressive.

1638
01:57:10,323 --> 01:57:11,860
Now feast your eyes on this.

1639
01:57:11,860 --> 01:57:14,409
Wow... not so impressive.

1640
01:57:14,440 --> 01:57:15,702
Since you're alive again,

1641
01:57:15,800 --> 01:57:18,310
Will you please help teach me how to study.

1642
01:57:18,399 --> 01:57:19,697
Of course, no problem.

1643
01:57:23,263 --> 01:57:25,823
So uh, you're giving school another shot?

1644
01:57:25,880 --> 01:57:29,320
Yeah I decided to take a cue from Shoko.

1645
01:57:30,320 --> 01:57:33,260
I figured... at least I could do this try.

1646
01:57:33,708 --> 01:57:35,727
I don't want to let you went down.

1647
01:57:37,862 --> 01:57:40,330
Isn't your big school festival tomorrow?

1648
01:57:40,355 --> 01:57:41,457
Oh yeah, that's right.

1649
01:57:47,540 --> 01:57:48,554
<i>"Hello, everyone said they
are going to the school festival</i>

1650
01:57:48,579 --> 01:57:49,687
<i>tomorrow. I will meet you at the
front gate at 10:00, is that OK?"</i>

1651
01:57:50,820 --> 01:57:52,946
Ha, good morning, everybody!

1652
01:57:52,980 --> 01:57:55,850
Up top! Yeah! Ha ha ha.

1653
01:57:56,260 --> 01:57:58,756
I said horrible things and I'm sorry.

1654
01:58:06,940 --> 01:58:07,786
Okay!

1655
01:58:08,240 --> 01:58:09,195
I'm heading out!

1656
01:58:09,360 --> 01:58:10,617
Have a good day, sweetheart!

1657
01:58:10,720 --> 01:58:11,303
Oh!

1658
01:58:11,640 --> 01:58:14,580
I see now! So that's what you're
supposed to do with those things.

1659
01:58:14,580 --> 01:58:15,285
What's that?

1660
01:58:15,480 --> 01:58:17,506
Nothing. I'll see you later okay?

1661
01:58:17,900 --> 01:58:20,105
Have a good day, Sho-Sho!

1662
01:58:34,980 --> 01:58:36,609
There you are!

1663
01:58:40,139 --> 01:58:41,399
Okay, let's go.

1664
01:58:50,960 --> 01:58:52,245
Isn't that Shoya?

1665
01:58:53,560 --> 01:58:54,080
Who's that?

1666
01:58:54,080 --> 01:58:57,234
Wait the one who was in the
hospital right? The guy who jumped?

1667
01:58:57,280 --> 01:58:58,207
Oops...

1668
01:59:02,560 --> 01:59:04,645
You probably didn't know this,

1669
01:59:04,825 --> 01:59:07,365
but I don't really fit in at school.

1670
01:59:10,660 --> 01:59:14,684
It's cause I have trouble looking people in the eye.

1671
01:59:15,820 --> 01:59:19,359
So it's easier for me to just
stare at the floor all the time.

1672
01:59:22,506 --> 01:59:24,402
You think it's okay to do that?

1673
01:59:26,920 --> 01:59:28,340
Aha Shoko...

1674
01:59:28,840 --> 01:59:31,480
I can actually do it without you leading me.

1675
01:59:31,940 --> 01:59:32,942
Thank you.

1676
01:59:34,047 --> 01:59:35,479
This is my classroom here.

1677
01:59:37,380 --> 01:59:40,463
Has the water boiled guys? It
just was just a few more minutes.

1678
01:59:41,174 --> 01:59:43,922
Oh wow, Shoya is back to school.

1679
01:59:43,947 --> 01:59:45,407
Are you okay now?

1680
01:59:47,565 --> 01:59:48,805
You know what?

1681
01:59:49,520 --> 01:59:52,262
I think my stomach is acting up a bit.

1682
01:59:54,184 --> 01:59:54,781
Sorry.

1683
01:59:55,174 --> 01:59:56,240
Ya-sho!

1684
01:59:56,589 --> 01:59:57,256
Huh?

1685
02:00:09,450 --> 02:00:10,237
Ya-sho?

1686
02:00:11,920 --> 02:00:13,780
Oh hey, that's Nagatsuka?

1687
02:00:13,887 --> 02:00:15,698
You're feeling okay?

1688
02:00:18,600 --> 02:00:19,601
Ya-sho.

1689
02:00:20,260 --> 02:00:23,751
Good morning Nagatsuka, good
to see you. So how is everything?

1690
02:00:23,953 --> 02:00:27,148
About that, what's going on? Why won't you look at me.

1691
02:00:27,453 --> 02:00:29,594
I don't know. I just feel weird.

1692
02:00:30,253 --> 02:00:33,682
I made myself a promise I would
look people in the eyes from now on.

1693
02:00:34,240 --> 02:00:35,532
Guess I'm too chicken...

1694
02:00:35,620 --> 02:00:37,305
Hey, Ya-sho...!

1695
02:00:37,938 --> 02:00:38,884
Shoya!!

1696
02:00:39,724 --> 02:00:42,348
You are okay, I'my glad.

1697
02:00:43,902 --> 02:00:44,879
Guess if you...

1698
02:00:45,219 --> 02:00:52,343
Cause if you didn't wake up, I don't know what I would
do. You are everything to me. I would've been all alone.

1699
02:00:52,738 --> 02:00:54,962
Listen, the stuff on the bridge,

1700
02:00:55,040 --> 02:00:56,675
don't worry about okay?

1701
02:00:56,800 --> 02:01:01,220
Friends say stuff they don't mean to
each other all the time! It doesn't matter.

1702
02:01:01,256 --> 02:01:02,582
I'm begging you...

1703
02:01:02,660 --> 02:01:04,820
don't ever leave us again.

1704
02:01:04,845 --> 02:01:05,620
Promise me,

1705
02:01:05,620 --> 02:01:07,020
I can't lose you.

1706
02:01:07,020 --> 02:01:08,116
It's gonna be okay.

1707
02:01:10,260 --> 02:01:12,292
Hey look, I'm sorry.

1708
02:01:13,032 --> 02:01:14,632
I mean,

1709
02:01:15,140 --> 02:01:18,025
thank you for being a friend.

1710
02:01:18,506 --> 02:01:19,766
You're very welcome!

1711
02:01:19,880 --> 02:01:22,756
But uh what's up with the facial hair?

1712
02:01:23,260 --> 02:01:27,477
That's my lucky stash I swore. I
wasn't shaving it till you woke up.

1713
02:01:27,910 --> 02:01:29,185
You did that for me...

1714
02:01:33,820 --> 02:01:34,488
Huh?

1715
02:01:35,599 --> 02:01:36,499
What's going on?

1716
02:01:36,573 --> 02:01:39,396
We heard Nagatsuka-kun's howling
your name so we followed him.

1717
02:01:41,766 --> 02:01:42,591
I see.

1718
02:01:43,400 --> 02:01:45,872
Miki did you bring the stuff to give to Shoya?

1719
02:01:47,664 --> 02:01:48,675
I brought them...

1720
02:01:48,822 --> 02:01:51,640
But I can't give it to him. It's a total failure.

1721
02:01:51,640 --> 02:01:53,767
Don't be silly, hand him over.

1722
02:01:59,980 --> 02:02:00,876
Here...

1723
02:02:02,300 --> 02:02:04,392
There's supposed to be a thousand of them,

1724
02:02:04,606 --> 02:02:06,592
but I couldn't finish it fast enough.

1725
02:02:07,400 --> 02:02:10,090
Everyone worked really hard. Did their best.

1726
02:02:10,115 --> 02:02:11,671
But we just couldn't...

1727
02:02:11,717 --> 02:02:13,419
No! This is amazing

1728
02:02:13,519 --> 02:02:14,756
It's more than enough.

1729
02:02:14,860 --> 02:02:16,993
No one's ever done anything like this for me.

1730
02:02:17,179 --> 02:02:19,053
It really means a lot seriously.

1731
02:02:19,520 --> 02:02:20,984
Thank you Miki.

1732
02:02:21,253 --> 02:02:22,774
And, I am sorry. Also... sorry.

1733
02:02:23,260 --> 02:02:24,307
And you too.

1734
02:02:24,719 --> 02:02:26,940
No worries, it's all good bro.

1735
02:02:27,920 --> 02:02:28,559
Ugh!

1736
02:02:28,730 --> 02:02:29,540
Enough!

1737
02:02:29,610 --> 02:02:32,540
All these every talk. I'm gonna lose my lunch.

1738
02:02:32,540 --> 02:02:35,028
Why do you always have to be like that, Naoka?

1739
02:02:35,520 --> 02:02:38,940
What? You got a problem with me
or something? You pick up a fight?

1740
02:02:38,940 --> 02:02:41,113
Okay everybody just calm down!

1741
02:02:41,363 --> 02:02:42,957
Oh... Shoya.

1742
02:02:43,420 --> 02:02:45,254
Listen I'm really sorry.

1743
02:02:45,665 --> 02:02:48,585
After all you've been through you really needed a friend,

1744
02:02:49,426 --> 02:02:51,303
but all I did was run away.

1745
02:02:52,540 --> 02:02:53,499
That's okay.

1746
02:02:54,300 --> 02:02:55,680
I did the same thing.

1747
02:02:57,106 --> 02:03:00,190
Stop acting so worried they're just talking things out.

1748
02:03:02,687 --> 02:03:04,122
You apologizing?

1749
02:03:05,420 --> 02:03:08,199
Well. Yes that's all you know how to do.

1750
02:03:08,756 --> 02:03:10,824
Mo-ron!

1751
02:03:15,351 --> 02:03:17,031
Mo-ron!

1752
02:03:17,588 --> 02:03:18,722
Moron!

1753
02:03:19,355 --> 02:03:20,015
Eh...

1754
02:03:26,160 --> 02:03:27,026
Whatever,

1755
02:03:27,140 --> 02:03:28,480
I'm gonna go find somebody.

1756
02:03:28,480 --> 02:03:29,760
Did she just run away?

1757
02:03:29,760 --> 02:03:31,290
I think she's embarrassed.

1758
02:03:34,360 --> 02:03:35,175
Hey guys,

1759
02:03:35,520 --> 02:03:37,439
I have a big favor to ask all of you.

1760
02:03:38,240 --> 02:03:39,047
That's okay?

1761
02:03:40,670 --> 02:03:43,636
Do you wanna go together to the festival?

1762
02:03:43,863 --> 02:03:44,880
How's that sound?

1763
02:04:03,940 --> 02:04:06,200
OMG, this is so good.

1764
02:04:06,200 --> 02:04:08,554
Oh, hey! Let's go to the gym next!

1765
02:04:08,760 --> 02:04:10,460
